page.title: 08Communications,Wick
page.content:
It trips in within ten seconds and is powered by acid batteries. There is a staff of 21 including only one woman.They have no regular shifts but there are three men on night duty and ten men working during the day.
Three public telephone kiosks may be used at a minimum charge of 10 pence. Two mail deliveries are made daily by the General Post Office and one collection is made from post boxes. These boxes vary from round freestanding objects to rectangular holes in the wall.Both are painted red.
